  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Criminalization of money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory compliance departments\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Business license revocation\n- Individual professional sanctions\n\n6. Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive legal and regulatory standards.",
